      "stem": "A student is deciding how long to study for a final exam. The expected score gain per hour of study is: 1. Hour 1: +8 points\n2. Hour 2: +5 points\n3. Hour 3: +3 points\n4. Hour 4: +1 point\n5. Hour 5: 0 points (asleep at desk) The alternative to studying any given hour is sleep, which the student values at the equivalent of 2 score points (sleep also improves next-day performance). 1. Compute the optimal number of hours of study and show your work.\n2. Explain in one sentence why studying for 4 hours instead of 3 would leave the student worse off, using the words *marginal benefit* and *marginal cost*.",
