      "mode": "short",
      "tags": [
        "U13",
        "CLO-5"
      ],
      "stem": "Classify each of the following goods using the rivalry-excludability framework. Label each as a *private good*, *public good*, *club good*, or *common resource*. For each, write one short sentence explaining your classification. 1. A Costco membership (warehouse access).\n2. A bottle of water from a vending machine.\n3. The Earth's atmosphere as a carbon-emissions sink.\n4. A free city park with no entry gate.",
      "model_answer": "1. Club good. Excludable (Costco checks membership at the door) but non-rival up to capacity (one member's shopping doesn't generally prevent another's, within the warehouse's footprint). 2. Private good. Excludable (the vending machine takes payment) and rival (one bottle bought is one bottle gone). 3. Common resource. Non-excludable (no one can fence off the atmosphere) but rival (each tonne of carbon emitted reduces the atmosphere's remaining capacity to absorb more without warming). 4. Public good (locally; or club good if you're strict about local taxpayers funding it). Non-excludable (no gate) and largely non-rival up to crowding (one person walking the path doesn't diminish another's enjoyment).",
      "key_points": [
        "bread: private (excl, rival)",
        "streaming: club (excl, non-rival)",
        "fishery: common (non-excl, rival)",
        "air quality: public (non-excl, non-rival)"
      ],
      "grading_notes": "per item: for correct classification, for correct excludability/rivalry call, for one-sentence justification. Common errors: streaming as private (forgetting non-rivalry), fishery as public (forgetting rivalry).",
      "review": [
        {
          "label": "OpenStax: cumulative review across assigned chapters",
          "url": "https://openstax.org/books/principles-microeconomics-3e/pages/1-introduction"
        },
        {
          "label": "MRU \u2014 Principles of Microeconomics",
          "url": "https://mru.org/principles-economics-microeconomics"
        }
      ]
