      "stem": "The market for bottled water has demand $Q_d = 200 - 4P$ and supply $Q_s = 6P - 100$, with $P$ in dollars and $Q$ in thousands of bottles. A heat wave shifts demand to the right; the new demand is $Q_d' = 230 - 4P$. Compute the new equilibrium quantity $Q^*$.",
      "model_answer": "Set new demand equal to supply: \\$230 - 4P = 6P - 100$, so \\$330 = 10P$ and $P^* = 33$. Then $Q^* = 230 - 4(33) = 230 - 132 = 98$. Check on supply: $Q^* = 6(33) - 100 = 198 - 100 = 98$. Match.",
