      "stem": "A frost destroys a large share of the orange crop. Demand for orange juice does not change. What does the standard model predict for the equilibrium in the orange-juice market?",
      "options": [
        {
          "letter": "A",
          "text": "Price rises; quantity rises.",
          "comment": "Both rising is the demand-right case, not the supply-left case."
        },
        {
          "letter": "B",
          "text": "Price rises; quantity falls.",
          "comment": "Correct. A leftward supply shift with demand fixed raises price and lowers quantity."
        },
        {
          "letter": "C",
          "text": "Price falls; quantity falls.",
          "comment": "Both falling is the demand-left case, not the supply-left case."
        },
        {
          "letter": "D",
          "text": "Price falls; quantity rises.",
          "comment": "Both moves in opposite directions like this is the supply-right case, not supply-left."
        }
      ],
      "answer": "B",
